{"timestamp": "2025-12-04 23:10:12.855339", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\n\nScope and view\n- Topology: 3-stage Clos (EBGP) with one super-spine (AS 65000), two spines, and two leaves. Each leaf hosts one /24 toward an attached host.\n- Hosts in focus: pc_0_0 (attached to leaf_router_0_0), pc_0_1 (attached to leaf_router_0_1).\n\n1) Anomaly detection\n- End-to-end reachability tests show the fabric is broadly healthy, but pc_0_1 exhibits complete loss of connectivity:\n  - Automated reachability matrix recorded “unknown” for pc_0_1 as a source.\n  - Direct tests from pc_0_1:\n    - ping 10.0.0.1 (its configured default gateway) fails 100% loss.\n    - ping 10.0.1.1 (the leaf it is physically connected to) returns “Destination Host Unreachable.”\n- Suspicious result: pc_0_0 → pc_0_1 is reported as successful with very low RTT. However, both pc_0_0 and pc_0_1 share the same IP (10.0.0.2), so that test actually pinged the local address on pc_0_0 and does not reflect real inter-host reachability.\n\n2) Fault localization\n- Control plane: All EBGP sessions across the fabric are established and carrying full routes:\n  - leaf_router_0_0: 8 neighbors up; receiving 31 prefixes; FRR “show ip route” has complete coverage for all 10.<pod>.<leaf>.0/24 networks.\n  - leaf_router_0_1: 8 neighbors up; receiving 31 prefixes; also shows full 10.x.x.0/24 coverage.\n  - spines and super-spine have their BGP adjacencies up and routing tables populated. ECMP is present at the super-spine toward downstream prefixes.\n- Data plane: pc_0_0 has correct local connectivity and can reach remote subnets (e.g., 10.1.3.2).\n- The connectivity failure is localized to the end host pc_0_1 and its directly connected segment, not the fabric.\n\n3) Root cause analysis\n- Host IP configuration inconsistency on pc_0_1:\n  - pc_0_1 is configured with IP 10.0.0.2/24 and default via 10.0.0.1.\n  - Physical attachment is to leaf_router_0_1, whose host-facing SVI is 10.0.1.1/